The majority element is the element that appears more than `n/2` times, where `n` is the length of the array.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef find_majority_element(nums: list[int]) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `nums` (list[int]): A list of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the majority element in the input list. If no majority element exists, return `None`.\", \"code\": \"def find_majority_element(nums: list[int]) -> int:\\n    counts = {}\\n    for num in nums:\\n        if num in counts:\\n            counts[num] += 1\\n        else:\\n            counts[num] = 1\\n    for num, count in counts.items():\\n        if count > len(nums) // 2:\\n            return num\\n    return None\", \"tests\": [\"assert find_majority_element([3, 2, 3]) == 3\", \"assert find_majority_element([2, 2, 1, 1, 1, 2, 2]) == 2\", \"assert find_majority_element([1, 2, 3]) is None\"] }"
